@kvhnuke  Excuse me for asking a silly question. In the example on top of this issue page, we have this signing data:

`0xec098504a817c800825208943535353535353535353535353535353535353535880de0b6b3a764000080318080`

Note the last three is `318080`. Given CHAIN_ID is 1, shouldn't [1, 0, 0] be encoded to `018080`?
